snippet: A new study suggests that an injectable, hormonal contraceptive popular with African women has biological properties that may make women and men more vulnerable to H.I.V. infection.
lead_paragraph: A new study suggests that an injectable, hormonal contraceptive popular with African women has biological properties that may make women and men more vulnerable to H.I.V. infection.

headline.main: Contraceptive Used in Africa May Double Risk of H.I.V.
headline.print_headline: Contraceptive Said to Double Risks of H.I.V.
